understanding about what the ancient JudeoChristian religion really was
about.  I expanded my research to cover the Apocrypha, the pseud., and
later into medieval grimoires and then through all different religious
texts.  I finally decided that I had to read everybody's claims, but
then had to make up my own mind.

This idea that the Hebrews and Egyptians expressed their emotions with
their liver was one of the confirmations in my early development that
other people would withhold the truth "for my own good", and that I had
to fight for my own understanding, because nobody else cared if I
understood or not.  All they wanted was my agreement with their
conclusions.
