Transhumanism is humanism without the limits imposed by a narrow
definition of "human."  Why must a humans die?  Why must humans feel
pain? Why must a human be made of flesh?  These are the questions that
transhumanists ask each other and themselves every day, and the questions
that humanists gave up on millenia ago.

