Transhumanism describes-- it describes a general covergence of values
among like-minded individuals. It describes a unrelenting desire to live
and a defiant disregard for the present limits of the human race.
  
Religions dictate-- they dictate rules, morales, and values.  They 
dictates how to live and how to die.
 
