I think this is a dangerous position. You can't communicate intuitive
insights, verbalizations are unwieldy to prepare and even more to 
consume. A graph or a table of numbers are much more succinct, and 
less prone to misinterpretation. I'm notoriously wary of number
toters, and those who believe (analytical) mathematics is perfectly 
applicable to the real world (usually it isn't). Yet, I think much 
could be gained if there was a common communicable 
calculus/formalization. Perhaps an augmenting reality device 
(current model: wearable with a HUD/Twiddler/myopotential input) could be 
